channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: The latest on Russia's war in Ukraine
item.description: Russia is pushing into northeastern Ukraine near Kharkiv after making several major advances there over the past week. Follow for live updates.

item.title: House GOP pushes bill to force Biden to continue transfer of weapons to Israel
item.description: The House plans to vote on a GOP bill to force the Biden admin to continue the transfer of weapons to Israel and to condemn its decision to pause a bomb shipment.

item.title: May 14, 2024 Israel-Hamas war
item.description: Amid signs that Israel may launch a full-scale incursion in Rafah, aid agencies are warning any escalation in the southern Gaza city risks exacerbating the already deteriorating humanitarian situation.

item.title: Inflation expected to have cooled slightly in April
item.description: Price increases have defied the Fed's aggressive cooldown efforts.

item.title: Trump defense cross-examines Michael Cohen in hush money trial
item.description: Donald Trump's defense will continue to cross-examine Michael Cohen on Thursday as it aims to discredit the prosecution's key witness in the former president's criminal hush money trial in New York.

item.title: Air Force pilot dies after aircraft ejection seat goes off while on the ground
item.description: An Air Force instructor pilot has died after the ejection seat on his aircraft activated while the plane was operating on the ground, officials said.

item.title: May 14, 2024 - Russia's war in Ukraine
item.description: Antony Blinken met with Volodymyr Zelensky in Kyiv earlier Tuesday, where the Ukrainian president told the US secretary of state that Ukraine urgently needs more air defenses.

item.title: Boeing breached 2021 deferred prosecution agreement: DOJ
item.description: Federal prosecutors have given Boeing until June 13 to respond to their determination.

item.title: May 13, 2024 Israel-Hamas war
item.description: The Biden administration has assessed that Israel has amassed enough troops on the edge of Rafah to move forward with a full-scale incursion in the coming days, but senior US officials are currently unsure if Israel has made a final decision to carry out such a move.

item.title: Pregnant woman, unborn child killed by falling tree during severe weather
item.description: Three people were killed in Louisiana -- including a pregnant woman and her unborn child -- due to severe weather on Monday, officials said.
